name: DJ Moore
summary: Wide receiver DJ Moore has signed a record-breaking four-year, $110 million contract extension with the Chicago Bears. This deal makes Moore the highest-paid player in Bears franchise history. The move is unusual for the Bears, who typically wait for players to finish their contracts before signing them to extensions. However, Moore's exceptional performance and potential warranted the exception. With this contract, Moore will become one of the highest-paid wide receivers in the NFL. The agreement has implications for fantasy football, as Moore's increased value is expected to benefit his team and potentially concern opponents.

summary: The United States women's rugby sevens team has made history by winning its first Olympic medal, a bronze. After advancing to the medal rounds with a Quarterfinal win, the team played New Zealand in the semifinals and Australia in the bronze medal match. Ilona Maher, a star on the team, has become a TikTok sensation leading up to the 2024 Paris Olympics. The historic win has garnered a $4 million donation to the team. The team's success is particularly notable for Sarah Levy, who played rugby at Northeastern University before her Olympic victory. Burlington native Ilona Maher and her team's bronze medal win against Australia has brought pride and recognition to their hometown.

name: Boar's Head recall
summary: There has been a Listeria outbreak linked to meats sliced at delis, according to the CDC. The source has been identified as Boar's Head meat products, and the company has recalled over 7 million pounds of deli meat and poultry products. The initial recall was for 200,000 pounds, which has since been expanded to include additional products. The recall affects multiple states, and a map is available to show which areas are affected. Consumers are advised to check their refrigerators for any Boar's Head products and to return them to the store for a refund. The outbreak has raised concerns about the safety of deli meats, and Boar's Head is working with the CDC to investigate the source of the contamination.
